ds the discussion to include contrasting exhibitions of photographs of atrocities committed by the German army on the Eastern Front during World War II, as well as to photographs taken at the Khmer Rouge S-21 torture and killing center. With an insightful blending of theoretical and qualitative analysis, Simon proposes new conceptualizations for a contemporary public pedagogy dedicated to bearing witness to the documents of racism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aHistoriography. 0aMuseum exhibitsxSocial aspects. 0aPublic history. 0aSocial justicexPsychological aspects. 4aAfrican American Studies : African American Studies. 4aAmerican Studies : American Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aEducation : Education. 4aHistory : American History. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh1 aPaolantonio, Mario Di, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2014z978311149015140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438452715423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438452715/original  a978-3-11-149015-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles